    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi @Texnomic - this was an early design of stopping all calls for the time when we sync from DB.\r\nSyncing from the DB happens when you stop the node during archive sync while the blocks have already been downloaded from the network. Since these blocks can be then processed entirely offline, we shut down networking while doing it to speed up the sync.\r\n\r\nWe have seen in the past that it was an undesired behaviour for some users so if you could express your opinion here we would appreciate as we may potentially change this behaviour.",
